plate.\n- Search Form: This form allows users to search for specific project templates by entering keywords in the search input field and clicking the search button.\n- Project Template List: This list displays the available project templates. Each project template is represented as a list item with a clickable link. The list items contain the following elements:\n   - Project Template Title: The title of the project template.\n   - Last Modified Date: The date when the project template was last modified.\n   - Project Template Description: A brief description of the project template.\n\n**Example Project Templates:**\n- Short Story: A brief work of fiction that is usually written in prose. It\'s typically focused on a single event or character.\n- Novel or Novella: A lengthy work of fiction characterized by its intricate plot, multifaceted characters, and exploration of various themes.\n- Flash Fiction: A very brief work of fiction, notable for its brevity and focused storytelling.\n- Picture Book: A type of book, usually designed for children, where illustrations and visuals play a significant role in storytelling.\n- Interactive Fiction: A narrative-driven game or story where the reader or player can interact with the story and make choices that affect the outcome.\n- Screenplay (Movie): A written work by screenwriters for a film, including dialogue, stage directions, and scene descriptions.\n- Episodic Screenplay or Series: The written work for television or streaming series, consisting of multiple episodes or seasons.\n- Radio Play or Podcast: A written narrative specifically crafted for auditory presentation, usually in the form of a radio play or podcast script.\n- Three-Act Play: A structured theatrical performance that divides the narrative into three distinct acts.\n- Musical or Opera: A written work for a musical or opera, combining spoken dialogue, songs, and musical numbers.\n\nPlease let me know if you need any further assistance.','2023-10-24 06:43:39